MALAYSIA DAYBOOK: Notion VTEC Helps Out Nikon, AmBank Term Loan

-- B y   B a r r y   P o r t e r
-- 
2011-03-20T21:37:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-20/malaysia-daybook-notion-vtec-helps-out-nikon-ambank-term-loan.html
Notion VTEC Bhd. (NVB MK), a
Malaysian metal processor and tools maker, said it will make
camera body mounts for Nikon Corp. following damage to some of
the Japanese company’s plants in last week’s earthquake and
tsunami.  This new business is expected to contribute as much as 60
million ringgit in annual sales, Notion VTEC said in an exchange
filing.  WHAT TO WATCH:
* Gema Padu Sdn. to announce plans for a 170 million ringgit
($56 million) sukuk program guaranteed by Danajamin Nasional Bhd.
at 10.45 a.m.
* AmBank Bhd. has hired five banks to help get a $210 million
three-year term loan, a person familiar with the matter said.
* RAM Rating Services Bhd. will give a banking sector update at
10 a.m.
* Feb. 1-20 palm oil export data from Intertek after 9:30 a.m.
and from Societe Generale de Surveillance after 12:30 p.m.  MARKETS:
*  Malaysia ’s FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI Index rose 0.8 percent.
* The MSCI Asia Pacific Index increased 0.4 percent.
* The  Dow Jones Industrial Average  gained 0.7 percent.
* Palm oil May-delivery futures advanced 3.4 percent to 3,473
ringgit a metric ton.  BTV (KL time):  7:10 a.m.: Former Nuclear Operator Michael Friedlander
7:40 a.m.: JPMorgan Chief Asian/Emerging Markets Strategist
Adrian Mowa
8:10 a.m.: Citigroup Head of FX Strategy for Asia Todd Elmer
8:40 a.m.: Synovate MD Klaus Paur 9:10 a.m.: Deutsche Bank Head
of Commodities Soozhana Choi
9:40 a.m.: Market Force Chairman/CEO James Roon
10:10 a.m.: RBS Asia Regional Strategist Emil Wolter
